        </div>
        <div class="partition">
            <h2>Viewport</h2>
            <p>The meta viewport gives information about the initial size of the viewport. It is used by mobile devices only.</p>
            <p><strong>Accessibility tip:</strong> Never use <code>maximum-scale=1.0</code>. It prevents the user from zooming in on the website, causing an accessibility issue.</p>
            <pre>
            <code>
            &lt;head&gt;
                ...
                &lt;!-- Viewport for responsive web design --&gt;
                &lt;meta name="viewport" content="key=value, key=value"&gt;
            &lt;/head&gt;
        </code>
    </pre>
            <p>
                Resources:
                <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Viewport_meta_tag">Responsive Design With Viewport Control</a>
            </p>
        </div>

