        <div class="partition">
            <h2>Header Tag</h2>
            <p>The <code>&lt;header&gt;</code> HTML tag element is used to identify the top of a webpage, article, section, or other segment of a page. The header is normally always the same across all pages of your website.</p>
            <p>
                Usage:
                <ul>
                    <li>Logo of the website</li>
                    <li>Navigation</li>
                    <li>Search form</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <pre>
            <code>
            &lt;body&gt;
                &lt;header&gt;This is my header&lt;header/&gt;
            &lt;/body&gt;
        </code>
    </pre>
            <p><strong>Warning!</strong> The <code>main</code> element should never be a descendant of an <code>article</code>, <code>aside</code>, <code>header</code>, <code>footer</code>, or <code>nav</code> element.</p>
            <p>
